<h2 class="shadow">Unix Commands</h2>

		<p>I was practicing the Unix commands and i have found an interesting command.
<br>
<h3>Hiding : </h3>


To create a file/directory as a hidden file/directory , just add dot (.) operator in front  of the file name. Thats gives you the hidden file.
<h4>
Example:</h4>

        $touch .filename.txt     # This is example to create the hidden file<br>
        $mkdir .directory         # This is example to create the hidden directory<br>

To view the hidden files in unix,<br>

        $ls -al                            #This displays all the hidden files/directories <br>
       <br> 

<h3>UnHiding :</h3>

  To make hidden file unhide, we need to simply rename the file using the mv command.<br>

<h4>Example:</h4>

       $mv .hidden-file.txt new-file.txt      #This is the example for a file<br>
       $mv .hidden-directory  unhidden-directory <br>
</p>


